Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.32,0:32:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,his wife God it's so stupid\Nhe's all upset about politics and she's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.76,0:32:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not interested in politics are you\Ninterested in politics
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.72,0:32:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No excitement about the late nose. Oh\Nwell. So
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.60,0:32:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,radical subjectivity then is the very\Nessence of experiencing the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.20,0:32:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God as\Nthat which says I.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.00,0:32:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That which allows you to be aware of\Nyour own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.36,0:33:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is at all times present,\Nnever absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.27,0:33:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first thing you become aware of\Nwhen you wake up in the morning. First
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.67,0:33:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that happens before thinking this\Neven starts is the awareness of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.51,0:33:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. Is the awareness of\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.72,0:33:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an awareness\Nas you wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.36,0:33:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that one exists. You don't even have a\Nname yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.64,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If I catch you the very first incident,\Nyou open your eyes, say, "What's your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.36,0:33:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,name?" Then give me a second while I\Nwake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.27,0:33:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a second. Are you man or woman?\NWait, give me a second till I wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.44,0:33:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you American or European? What are\Nyou? Give me a second to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.08,0:33:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is there before even\Ncontent. Consciousness awakens
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.67,0:33:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then with the awareness of existence.\NThat which allows you to say I
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.20,0:34:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is presumed as you wake up to be the\Npersonal eye
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.44,0:34:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because reality\Nseems to have to do with form and facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.15,0:34:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and physicality.\NOne presumes that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.20,0:34:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that I am, that I exist, being\Naware,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.63,0:34:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of eye is coming from a\Npersonal eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.96,0:34:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the only illusion we have to\Njump.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.83,0:34:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of eye is not coming from a\Npersonal eye at all. It's coming from an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.11,0:34:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal eye.\NConsciousness is an impersonal quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.59,0:34:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness which arises as you\Nawaken is not personal at all. You have
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.59,0:35:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it focused on the personal\Nbut its essence is not personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.44,0:35:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of the infinite eye\Nthat which is not different than
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.20,0:35:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity, reality, truth, all the things\Nthat's been called throughout the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.83,0:35:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It illuminates the awareness\Nthat shines forth as the awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.52,0:35:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your own existence,\Nbut its source is the infinite eye. Is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.40,0:35:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that clear?\NThat which knows that you're here this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.76,0:35:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,second\Nis not the personal eye. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.56,0:35:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if we ablate the personal eye, you will\Nstill be aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.24,0:35:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one's quality is that of existence.\NIt was that dilemma that confronted me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.48,0:36:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at age three. People say they like to\Nhear personal stories and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.64,0:36:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the personal story is actually\Nirrelevant. But it it display it it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.96,0:36:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,gives an example of what we're talking\Nabout. In this lifetime at age three,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.83,0:36:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,out of complete oblivion and\Nnothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.11,0:36:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there was a shock.\NThis thing here was sitting in a little
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.76,0:36:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wagon\Nand I realized I exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.11,0:36:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the awareness of existence very\Nwith extreme clarity and extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.48,0:36:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,shockingly shocking intensity.\NNor was I pleased with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.56,0:36:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a shocking awareness of\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.24,0:36:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly arose a fear. If I had come\Ninto existence, then hypothetically
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.11,0:37:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it might have been that I might not have\Ncome into existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.32,0:37:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was really the awareness of\Nexistence as as beingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.07,0:37:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I amness.\NAt three, there was no verbalization
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.40,0:37:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about any of this, but it was a complete\Nunderstanding of it, let me tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.59,0:37:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really set the theme for this\Nlife lifetime for uh many years to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.07,0:37:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That dilemma of reality as existence\Nversus non-existence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.44,0:37:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is in an extremely abstract and\Nextremely high level. It's a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.96,0:37:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,paradox you don't have to solve until\Nyou get to level 890 or something
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.83,0:37:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which was difficult to handle there for\N8 days. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Um but the dilemma of existence versus\Nnon-existence was like a silent um
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.56,0:38:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,paradox you know that uh hung out in the\Nback of my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.48,0:38:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in the lifelong pursuit of\Nidentifying the radical truth of the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.72,0:38:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,self and who you are.\NAnd um it wasn't verbalized
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.76,0:38:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,again for many years.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.00,0:38:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nbut there was the paradox of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.72,0:38:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence.\NThe beautiful thing about realizing the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.72,0:38:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,truth of who you are, the truth of who\Nyou are is not different than
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.35,0:38:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that which subject subjectively is\Nconscious of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.07,0:38:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing needs to be said about it. It\Ndoesn't have to be searched for.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.16,0:39:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to study to find it.\NIt's more an intuitive awareness that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.88,0:39:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of dawns on you that that is the\Nultimate reality you've been searching
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.59,0:39:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for.\NThat ultimate reality
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.56,0:39:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is timeless. And as one becomes aware of\Nit, one realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.44,0:39:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which you really are has\Nalways existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.44,0:39:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will always exist because it is beyond\Nexistence versus non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.52,0:39:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is beyond time.\NIt is beyond form.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.28,0:39:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the substrate out of which all\Nexperiencing arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.40,0:39:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that solves all the riddles.\NNow religion says such a awareness is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.00,0:39:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not possible till you after you're dead\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.83,0:39:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in heaven or someplace.\NSo religion looks at God as
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.64,0:40:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,transcendent.\NThe transcendent God uh shows up in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.16,0:40:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis,\Ncreates the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.28,0:40:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,promptly disappears,\Nand goes in heaven, moved to heaven, and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't get any chance to meet him\Ntill after you're dead if you've been
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.24,0:40:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,good.\NThere is that horrible moment called
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.76,0:40:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,judgment day, though. Uh-oh.\NSo God rolls the dice, says, "Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.16,0:40:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You're on your own." Then he hangs out\Nin heaven waiting for you with a big
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.16,0:40:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,stick.\NAnd uh if you didn't do so well, wacko
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.48,0:40:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,into the boiling cauldron\Nout of which he gets great. By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.64,0:40:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he loves to see people suffer. Anyway,\Nhe picks the good and the bad or he
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.88,0:41:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,picks 144,000, whatever.\NWhere does that come from? 144,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.88,0:41:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Revelations.\N>> Oh, Revelations. Oh, okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.80,0:41:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, out of the billions and billions\Nand billions of souls, he picks this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.64,0:41:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,number. Anyway, anyhow,\Nso that is the God who is transcendent
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.28,0:41:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to be feared, projected somewhere\Nelsewhere in time and space
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.24,0:41:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because heaven is up there and you're\Ndown here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.92,0:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're down here and heaven god\Nis up there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances are not too good you're\Ngoing to run into him at the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.11,0:41:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart.\NSo, traditional real religion then is a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.59,0:41:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,denial of the reality of the truth of\Nyourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.88,0:42:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that is\Nin great contrast to the mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.07,0:42:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion therefore is\Nextremely limited as compared to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.92,0:42:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality.\NSo we differentiate between religion and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.04,0:42:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality.\NA very delicate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.35,0:42:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but important difference to be made.\NThe signers of the constitution
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.44,0:42:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,understood it perfectly. The\Nconstitution in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.92,0:42:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at over 700. That is\Nspiritual brilliance. That's the level
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.64,0:42:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sage, the genius.\NIt clearly differentiates spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.07,0:42:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom\Nfrom the establishment of religion and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.31,0:42:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,clearly saw that if anything, religion\Nis an enemy of spiritual freedom. Of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.11,0:43:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,course coming out of England and\NProtestant Catholic conflicts over the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.96,0:43:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,years etc. they were of course highly\Nconscious of that but I don't think it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.72,0:43:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,came out of their historical experience.\NIt came out of really a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.40,0:43:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,inspiration because the signers of the\NDeclaration of Independence etc all
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.80,0:43:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated in the high 500s. They were\Nreally extremely gifted men and we were
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.52,0:43:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we are very very fortunate. Constitution\NUnited States calibrates higher than the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.16,0:43:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,constitution of any country on the\Nplanet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.04,0:43:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It guarantees spiritual freedom and it\Ndoes so by prohibiting religion from
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.40,0:43:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming established and simultaneously\Nit does not prohibit religion. So it was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.56,0:43:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely brilliant and very few people\Ntoday really comprehend the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.68,0:43:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,between spiritual and religious.\NSo religion then becomes over time an
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.52,0:43:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,institution which has its upside and its\Ndownside.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.11,0:43:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In another book we're doing right now we\Ncalibrate the level of truth of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.88,0:44:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,world's great religions. And you can\Ntrack it down through time. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.92,0:44:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,track it down from the time of its\Norigination down through the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.72,0:44:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and down through the council of Trent,\Nthe council of na all the various things
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.40,0:44:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what happened to all the various\Nworld's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.31,0:44:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditionally the mystic has been um\Nat odds with traditional religion. In
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.35,0:44:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, some religions condemn the mystic\Nand historically mystics were burned at
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.68,0:44:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the stake and declared heretics etc.\NExcommunicated
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.80,0:44:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and put in strange places.\NIn some world's religions actually
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.76,0:44:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nthe the subjective reality of the mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:45:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is is declared to be formally heretic\Nheresy. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.72,0:45:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To experience the presence of God within\Nis actually forbidden
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.92,0:45:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in Islam for instance.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.56,0:45:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so the Christian mystic didn't do too\Nwell either.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.31,0:45:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The only place the mystic has really\Nprospered in history has been uh in the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.44,0:45:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,area in in India\Nwhere the tradition of the mystic is uh
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.59,0:45:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional. The vidas\Nthey explain the realization of the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.07,0:45:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God itself\Nuh for some thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.56,0:45:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All those by the way do calibrated at a\Nthousand as does the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.64,0:45:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who\Ncleverly got himself born in India
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.04,0:46:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he didn't get crucified for his\Nteachings. Had he been born elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.28,0:46:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he would not have fared as well. But\Nthere was already um a friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.59,0:46:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge of spiritual truth in that\Npart of the world of some of great
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.83,0:46:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,antiquity.\NSo what he taught was not at great odds
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.28,0:46:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with their tradition.\NAnd the land of the Buddha, the lands
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.40,0:46:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that are favorable to Buddhism are today\Nthe most favorable to the mystic
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.80,0:46:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when we speak in Korea, let's say, or\Nthe Orient. you know, they come by the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.31,0:46:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands from all over the country\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.88,0:46:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all we're saying is that we have sort of\Ndemonstrated in a scientific verifiable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.04,0:46:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,way what their culture has held to be\Nthe truth for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.00,0:46:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the prosperity of a religion or a\Nspiritual teaching depends considerably
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.44,0:47:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then on context on context. Not just on\Ncontent.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.88,0:47:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The religionist tends to emphasize\Ncontent
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.04,0:47:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and declare holy wars based on content\Nthereby negating the context. But it is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.35,0:47:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the context out of which their spiritual\Nteaching come is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.64,0:47:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Without context, what they're babbling\Nis nonsense. any mental hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.80,0:47:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that's full of religious people that can\Nbabble all kinds of religious stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.11,0:47:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the context that gives a spiritual\Nteaching any kind of validity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.24,0:47:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because God is the ultimate context.\NThat which is God deres it infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.28,0:47:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,power by the fact that divinity is\Ninfinite context.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.92,0:48:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of infinite context comes infinite\Npower.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.72,0:48:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So religion which negates context has\Njust negated its own validity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.04,0:48:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual seekers are made up\Nconsiderably by people who have had
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.52,0:48:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a variety of religious backgrounds\Nand many have ridden it as far as it can
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.80,0:48:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,go and then want to know\Nwhere do we go from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.64,0:48:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people have had subjective\Nspiritual experiences were which were
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.40,0:48:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,quite\Nquite powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.11,0:48:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime.\Nuh such things occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.07,0:48:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at age 12 or 14.\NA near-death experience which was
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.35,0:48:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,transformative totally eliminated the\Nfear of death
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.40,0:48:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,uh for the rest of my life.\NAnd in the late 30s, suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.31,0:49:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all that the mind had considered myself\Nin reality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.44,0:49:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,completely disappeared and\Nwas replaced by an infinite context
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.59,0:49:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which was\Nthe presence which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.31,0:49:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,swept away all thought.\NSo those kind of severe spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.40,0:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences then account for some of us\Nbeing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.00,0:49:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people become interested in\Nspiritual work because they have a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.07,0:49:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,variety of illnesses and they've heard\Nthat through spiritual investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.52,0:49:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,every illness known to mankind has been\Nknown to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.07,0:49:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,become healed and resolved and I myself\Nhave witnessed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.20,0:49:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true that with a certain with\Nintense spiritual work a certain
